<appendix id="cedar-depends">

   <title>Dependencies</title>

   <simplesect>

      <para>
         This appendix provides additional information about the software which
         Cedar Backup depends on, including information about how to find
         documentation and packages on non-Debian systems.
      </para>

      <varlistentry>
         <term>Python 2.3</term>
         <listitem>
            <para>
               Version 2.3 of the Python interpreter was released on 29 July 2003,
               so most <quote>current</quote> Linux distributions should include it.
               (Unfortunately, the current Debian stable release <quote>woody</quote>
               does <emphasis>not</emphasis> include it, but I have provided a 
               backport on cedar-solutions.com)
            </para>
            <para>
               The <quote>upstream</quote> home for Python is 
               <ulink url="http://www.python.org"/>
            </para>
